social_posts.post_text:
The Thanksgiving holiday may have passed…But EVERYDAY should be a day of Thanksgiving!

“For everything you’ve done for me, for everything you are to me, for everything you’ve given me… I’ve got to give you THANKS.” 

#WithThanksgiving #KurtCarrSingers

One of my favorite photos with my friend @MsGladysKnight from 2018. 

I still think Gladys and I need to get in the studio and work on a Gospel album for her. What do you think? #GladysKnight

I love Christmas music. And I miss my friend Natalie Cole so much! Her two Christmas albums are both great, you should add them to your Christmas rotation and playlists if you haven't.

#NatalieCole #Christmas
PHILADELPHIA: I’ll be there tomorrow, Dec. 13 at the @KimmelCulturalCampus! Come see me get honored.

MERRY CHRISTMAS Cousins! 🙏🏽🎄

"Joy to the world, the Lord is come/Let Earth receive her King/Let every heart prepare Him room/And Heaven and nature sing..."

Happy New Year Cousins! 🙌🏽 Here’s to the best year of our lives!!! 

#HappyNewYear

Some of you don’t realize that there’s been an attack on you already in 2023 and it didn’t have an impact because “God Blocked It!”

Thanks to @brittanyreevesmusic & @iamnikkipotts of the Kurt Carr Singers for helping to deliver this ministry message at @woffamily! 

#GodBlockedIt #KurtCarrSingers
Throwback Thursday: Dressed up & ready for church! 🙌🏽

social_posts.post_text:
SURPRISE: The Kurt Carr Singers have a new song. This is my “Word of Faith!” And that’s @singingro on lead vocals.

Do you like it? 

Will you sing it at your churches? 

I pray that it encourages your soul. 🙏🏽 #KurtCarrSingers

social_posts.post_text: Enjoy this snippet from a classic @WestAngelesCOGIC service with the Kurt Carr Singers. We’ve been singing “In The Sanctuary” a long time, and God is still using this song to Bless people! 🙌🏽

Celebrating the pastoral anniversary of Reverend Dr. Joe Samuel Ratliff of @brentwood_baptist in Houston with the Kurt Carr Singers.

Wonderful meeting Houston mayoral candidate @amandakedwardstx while there. #KurtCarrSingers

This young man @cortneyinspires came and blessed us at @uarkansas on “I Almost Let God.” Sir, you can SING! Thanks @jallenmurdock for the suggestion! #iAlmostLetGo

🎥 by @singingro

Behind every great talent are people behind the scenes working to make artists successful. @1bjeffrey was one of those people. One of the most-respected radio promotions execs in the music industry, it was my pleasure to work with and travel with Jeff Grant during my @VerityGospel - Zomba years.

Here we are at @SiriusXM and a photo he took of me.

Job well done Jeff! You’ve earned your wings! 🙏🏽 #RIP
I love when life and time seem to rhyme. #fullcircle #lsu #nationalchampions #coachmulkey

When God gave me the song “In The Sanctuary,” I never imagined the international impact it would have! That’s been a true blessing! 

Here are the Kurt Carr Singers in Africa at @TheGloriousFountain Ministries with their choir. 

#KurtCarrSingers #InTheSanctuary
In The Bahamas with the voice, @kimburrelllove! The endless laughs!
Remembering my mom, my beloved Delores Carr on this Mother’s Day! I miss you and love you! Happy Heavenly Mother’s Day! 🙏🏽💐 #MothersDay

I believe God
He is incredible, invincible
He can crumble the impossible
Yes, I believe God

#iBelieveGod
It’s always a good time with my best friend Ami Rushes (@arushes). We need to take more photos together… but here’s a throwback of us. #TBT

We had a time at the Spring Workshop in Montgomery, Alabama.

📸’s by @terronmedia

The Gospel Industry and the community of faith join together to collectively PRAY for our sister C. Ashley Brown-Lawrence (@sweetsingercece). You’ve been blessed by her ministry with my brother @bishophez and as a solo artist, now let’s petition heaven for her total healing! 🙏🏽 God Is a Healer! #iBelieveGod

Got to go check out John P. Kee (@keetwit) in concert in Houston! So good to see him, we’ve been friends more than 30 years!

His catalog of hits, the singing, his singers, the band… it was all amazing! He is the King of Gospel! #JohnPKee

My heart is broken. C. Ashley Brown-Lawrence (@sweetsingercece) was my niece. I've known and loved her since she was born. I know she's resting in heaven now, but this one hurts.

Pray for her husband, her family, friends and everyone her music ministry touched. 🙏🏽

I’m headed to Las Vegas. Meet me at the Opening Act Artist Showcase. They’re doing a Tribute to ME!

#KandDProductions  #OpeningActLasVegas
Today is @TheStellars in Las Vegas. I'm so grateful to have been inducted into the Stellar Honors Hall of Fame in 2018. What a Blessing! #StellarAwards

A snippet of me joining the Kurt Carr All-Star Singers for a special tribute to me during the #TheStellars in Las Vegas. We’re singing “Be Blessed,” a song I wrote for Bishop Paul S. Morton… but in all honesty, I was the one blessed by this tribute!

Thank You #OpeningActLasVegas and #KandDProductions for a wonderful night! 🙏🏽

One thing about being at #TheStellars is everywhere you go, you’ll bump into a Gospel legend. And I got to see @pastorscaesar, Dr. Bobby Jones, Tramaine Hawkins, Don Jackson of @TheStellars, @byroncage and got to see @vickimacklataillade be honored while being in Las Vegas.

Still reflecting on the great tribute to me during #TheStellars weekend in Las Vegas. Thanks to all of the Kurt Carr Singers that showed up to celebrate me.

And THANKS again to @justkhare & @dthompsonentertainment_ for making this happen! 

#OpeningActLasVegas #KandDProductions

We had a time at the Indiana Black Expo, Inc. (@inblackexpoinc)! The Kurt Carr Singers were one of the featured artists during the expo. Enjoy these snippets of “God Blocked It” (featuring @iamnikkipotts) and “I Almost Let Go” (featuring @kelikel98). #KurtCarrSingers

Found the perfect flashback image with the late, great Tony Bennett. I was saddened by his passing last week.

We did a few concerts together in Italy. He was ‘Uncle Tony’ to me. He called me ‘Gospel Guy.’

An impeccable vocalist. A great human. And a gentleman. 🙏🏽 #TonyBennett

During the tribute to me in Las Vegas, there was wonderful video paying homage to me from my friends, peers and even those from my church. This type of love means more than you know!

Thanks again @justkhare & @dthompsonentertainment_ of #OpeningActLasVegas and #KandDProductions for an awesome celebration and creating this amazing moment! 🙏🏽

God is going to show up right in the nick of time! His time is always impeccable!

How do you know Kurt? I’ve Seen Him Do It! 🙌🏽

The #KurtCarrSingers had a great time in Chicago at The Black Women’s Expo (@bwenext). There's just something about the people of #Chicago and their love for Gospel Music. 

And ministry is always easy with my amazing Kurt Carr Singers!
While in Chicago recently, the Kurt Carr Singers introduced our new song “Can God.” I hope you life it... we have new music coming soon and I believe it is really going to bless you! #KurtCarrSingers

I had the pleasure of teaching a course at @uarkansas for a Master of Music: Black Sacred Music.

Me, Kurt Carr, teaching a masters level college course? “I’ve Seen Him Do It!” 

It was humbling to be in the company of such great people. All God's favor! 

Thank You to Jeffrey Allen Murdock, Ph.D! 

#UArkansas #GospelMusic

Found this photo of my niece C. Ashley Brown-Lawrence (@Sweetsingercece) singing with me. 

So grateful that my final words to her the day before she went to heaven were, “I love you.”
 
Please cherish your loved ones! 🙏🏽

It was a 60th birthday service fit for a queen, and the royal vessel being celebrated was my anointed friend @JudithChristieMcAllister! 

I worked alongside this woman for 20 years at @WestAngelesCOGIC! 

I’ve said it before, and I’ll say it again, one day the history books of the Black church will talk about how she was at the forefront of the sound we now call “Praise and Worship.”

Happy Birthday Judy! So glad I was able to join the celebration!

Some of the greatest ministers of the Gospel gathered to salute our friend @JudithChristieMcAllister! 

And she deserves all of the love as she kicks off Chapter 60 of her life! 

(If you see someone you know, tag them in the comments!)
Sitting in gratitude that God has given me another trip around the sun. Thank You all for the Birthday love! It means more than you know! 🙏🏽💙 #Birthday

So inspiring seeing NBA great Stephen Curry being blessed by my music. His enjoyment of “In The Sanctuary” will introduce this song to a whole new generation of people. 

Thanks to @ThompsonScribe for sharing this video! 

#InTheSanctuary #StephCurry #DubNation

Sorry to hear about the passing of my friend & @pbs_1914 frat brother #DaveDickinson (@knowwax.dave.d).

Dave was a true music lover that served as a program director at @SiriusXM & hosted a weekend show on @HearHeartSoul.

So many artists owe a debt of gratitude to Dave. 🙏🏽 #RIP
The Lord has sent me some of the best singers in the world for the Kurt Carr Singers. Meet my newest member, your newest cousin, 23-year-old @lidyah.lee. She’s something special! #KurtCarrSingers

Kudos to producer @WarrynCampbell for his awesome remix of “For Every Mountain” on the “Kingdom Business: Season 2” soundtrack. The new version features @iamTytist & the #KingdomBusiness cast.

I love when a new generation can appreciate my music! 

#KurtCarr #ForEveryMountain
The men of the Kurt Carr Singers: @singingro @teeroybright & @theetravistaylor. Thanks for holding me down gentlemen. #KurtCarrSingers

I went to @TheReunionTourOfficial and it was great. @kirkfranklin did amazing job pulling it together.

#TheClarkSisters are the greatest of all time! #TamelaMann has one of my favorite church voices! And #DavidMann is hilarious! @davidandtamela 

@tyetribbett is soo anointed and such a trooper! @israelhoughton can sing his face off! The tour band and support singers were so on point!

An incredible night of Gospel Music! 🎶 #TheReunionTour

I love doing ministry with the Kurt Carr Singers! Just Thankful for them! 🙏🏽

We were together for the 40th Anniversary of Apostle Dr. Jimmie A Ellis and Victory Christian Center in Philadelphia (@vccbedrockswphilly)! 

#KurtCarrSingers #Thankful

The Kurt Carr Singers have been ministering my newest song, “Can God” while on the road and I promise you, it has been blessing the people! I hope it encourages you as well. 

This clip is from @vedabrown while we ministred for the 40th Anniversary of Apostle Dr. Jimmie A Ellis (@alphaomega5220) and @vccbedrockswphilly.

That’s @kelikel98 on lead vocals! #KurtCarrSingers

Went to see @samarajoysings I Believe God has gifted her with one of the most incredible voices I’ve ever heard! She is so young But will undoubtedly be named among the hallowed  legendary vocalists.

Her father, uncle and a cousins joined her on stage and they also sang  beautifully. The McClendon family singing gene is REAL!!!
Most importantly she’s a beautiful person who loves the Lord...I’m getting my pen ready to write her a song.  You ready Samara???♥️♥️♥️

Kicking off my favorite time of the year in Decatur, GA on December 7th at Impact Network’s Christmas Extravaganza an evening of gospel music honoring Dr. Bobby Jones with the amazing 
Dottie Peoples, Jekalyn Carr, Vickie Winans, Dorothy Norwood and more. Hosted by Dr. Teresa Hairston
I enjoyed celebrating my favorite time of the year at Epiphany benefit  concert at @thefountainofpraise What a wonderful night of music with @kimburrelllove, @kennylattimore , @raychewlive and more.
So much POWER on both sides of me, @kimburrelllove and @chrystalrucker .  I could barely stand it!! Both of these phenomenal ladies are unrivaled gifts to the body!!!I’m blessed to call both sisters.
If God has been good to you. #praisebreak

“Lord, I promise. Every time You bless. 
I’m gonna bless somebody else.” 

During this holiday season find a way to bless somebody else. This is the true meaning of Christmas. #blessed #christmas

So humbled to hear the incomparable @kimburrelllove lending her genius interpretation to For Every Mountain at @gospelfestivalparis with the awesome @totalpraisemasschoir.  What a Christmas gift. …. Bonjour a tous mesa mi Parisien.

Earlier this month we helped to celebrate Dr. Bobby Jones!  He is 85 years young and continuing to spread the gospel.  Thank you for your vision and legacy of spreading the word of God through music by introducing, and amplifying Gospel music into living rooms across the globe.

Late Post:  As the year comes to a close, I am counting my many blessings and thanking God for another year on this earth.  A couple of months ago My BFF Marichal Monts and Kim Walker did it; they surprised me for my birthday.  Thank you for gathering my family and friends.
Brought in the new year with The Kurt Carr Singers and my @woffamily family.  2023 had its challenges but God carried us through.  And we thank Him that we made it.  #happynewyear2024

Finishing touches on new music. They say I’m a perfectionist…lol….but my God deserves my best. And my loyal supporters  around the world patiently wait years in between projects so I do everything I can to bless and inspire.  Love you all. It’s coming😀!!
Happy Founders’ Day to my brothers of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, Inc! 110 years of culture for service, and service for humanity.  #Sigma110 #pbs1914
